The pairwise statistical significance of the prediction accuracy of the classifiers is examined using t-test for paired samples. T-test is commonly employed to assess if the difference between the performance of two classifiers over various data sets is random (Virtanen et al., 2020). The p-values, which are presented in Table 17, indicate the statistical significance between the prediction accuracy of HOPE and the rest of the classifiers for all three examined levels of complexity. It is shown most p-values are less than 0.05, which makes the differences statistically significant.Table 17
